# Cogniville Project

Unity 2D game (C#). Main flows: main menu → student name (PanelName) → book select → world/level → quiz battle → back to menu → results.

## Key paths
- **Scenes:** `Assets/Scenes/MainMenu.unity`, `WorldSelect.unity`, level scenes (e.g. `IceLevel1`)
- **Menu/UI:** `Assets/Scripts/UI/MainMenuController.cs`, `Assets/Scripts/UI/Panels/` (PrincipalPanel, ResultsPanel, SessionPanel)
- **Game data:** `Assets/Scripts/GameDataManager.cs` (singleton, DontDestroyOnLoad): player name, teacher list, session, results, leaderboard
- **Battle:** `Assets/Scripts/BATTLELOGIC/QuizBattle.cs` — calls `GameDataManager.Instance.SetGameResults(...)` and `BackToMenu()`
- **Editor helpers:** `Assets/Scripts/Editor/CognivilleUIMenu.cs` — Tools > Cogniville: apply UI font, button hover/press scale

## Panel names (main menu)
- **PanelName** = student name (before book select). **PanelLogin** = teacher login. **PanelPrincipal** = principal adds teachers. **PanelResult** / ResultsScreen = stats after level. Buttons: PrincipalButton, HomeButton, NextButton, BackButton; MainMenuController binds by name (TryBind) and auto-binds any button whose name contains "back".

## UI consistency
- **Font:** Large, readable text — size 32 for inputs, 30 for button labels. Use Tools > Cogniville to apply. See rule `ui-ux-consistency.mdc` for full checklist.
- **Buttons:** Same sprite and font on ALL buttons; hoverScaleAmount 1.1, scaleOnPress 1 (no shrink). Run **Apply standard UI (Play look)** and hover/press scale tools so every button matches.
- **Principal panel Back:** Bound in MainMenuController after fade to panelPrincipal (Find("BackButton") under panel).

## Teachers
- GameDataManager: `AddTeacher`, `RemoveTeacher`, `GetTeachers`, `IsAllowedTeacher`. Stored in PlayerPrefs. If list non-empty, only those teachers can log in.
